# 06.05 Testing Framework

## Overview

The Testing Framework defines how cmdOS validates system reliability, correctness, security, and performance throughout the development lifecycle.

Because cmdOS is an AI Execution Operating System, testing must cover not only traditional software components but also:

- AI systems
- Agent behavior
- Execution workflows
- Plugin ecosystem
- Security boundaries
- System integrations

Core principle:

Development

↓

Testing

↓

Validation

↓

Quality Assurance

↓

Production

---

# 1. Testing Framework Purpose

The purpose of the Testing Framework is to ensure that every cmdOS component operates correctly and reliably.

It enables:

- Bug detection
- System validation
- Security assurance
- Performance optimization
- Continuous improvement

---

